		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Do not listen to <strong>anything</strong> anyone here has to say* about this subject.<br /><br />Contact an attorney who is familiar with copyright law.  You should be able to find one online, or even in the yellow pages.  A good attorney will be willing to give you 15 minutes of their time to hear your questions and tell you whether or not you'd need to hire them (say, for an hour's worth of time) to get answers in full.<br /><br />* - Don't be tempted to be a smart ass and bring recursion into this (&quot;how can I trust what YOU say then!?&quot;)

		

